  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: b492ab769d202ee4183275be4bff9429, type: 3}
  m_Name: I Would Not Be A King
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::FlightPaper.ProjectSorrow.Poems.PoemScriptableObject
  id: 46
  title: I Would Not Be A King
  author: Percy Bysshe Shelley
  isFemaleAuthor: 0
  stanzas:
  - lines:
    - I would not be a king - enough
    - Of woe it is to love;
    - The path to power is steep and rough,
    - And tempests reign above.
    - I would not climb the imperial throne;
    - '''Tis built on ice which fortune''s sun'
    - Thaws in the height of noon.
    - Then farewell, king, yet were I one,
    - Care would not come so soon.
    - Would he and I were far away
    - Keeping flocks on Himalay!
  rating: 1
